estors get nothing, and the creditors get (1) the company, for whatever tha=
t=E2=80=99s worth, plus (2) the piles of cash raised from the meme-stock in=
vestors. My assumption is that AMC will use its long run as a meme stock to=
=C2=A0<em>solve=C2=A0</em>its financial problems, but the alternative is ba=
d.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"=
