_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">talked a few years ago</a> about how (1) venture =
capitalists, to stand out in a competitive field, =E2=80=9Chave to build pa=
rasocial relationships with founders=E2=80=9D by being cool on Twitter (now=
 X), because =E2=80=9CTwitter is the new social club,=E2=80=9D and (2) ther=
efore VCs hire ghostwriters to write cool tweets for them. Surely a large l=
anguage model could write tweets too. Venture capital is a process of funne=
ling money from big institutions to promising founders with good business i=
deas, and then helping those founders build their companies. If a robot can=
 find the promising ideas and advise the founders, maybe that process can b=
e automated.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspa=
